    <section>
        <h>uses</h>
        <section id="uses-predicate">
            <h>predicate</h>
            <p>Like other adjectives, <g>dubh</g> can be used (uninflected) as the predicate of the
                verb <a href="?gd=bi"><g>bi</g></a>.</p>
            <p>Some examples – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>A bheil an cù <m>dubh</m>?</gd>
                        <tr>Is the dog black?</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 13</ref>
                    </li>
                <li>
                    <gd>Tha seo <m>dubh</m> agus tha sin geal.</gd>
                    <tr>This (one) is black and that (one) is white.</tr>
                    <ref text="617">td. 15</ref>
                </li>
            </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
        <section id="uses-mod">
            <h>modifier</h>
            <p>Like other adjectives, <g>dubh</g> can be used as a modifier of a <a
                    href="?xx=nouns/nouns">noun</a></p>
            <p>Examples with masculine nouns – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha <m>falt dubh</m> air Calum.</gd>
                        <tr>Calum has black hair.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 9 [adapted]</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Chan eil an <m>cù dubh</m> anns an achadh an diugh.</gd>
                        <tr>The black dog is not in the field today.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 14 [227]</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
